c1=A.iZ("Key topic for Prelims (Economy) and Mains GS-III. RBI's CBDC framework, difference between CBDC and cryptocurrency, and impact on monetary policy are frequently tested.","",b9,"","The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has unveiled a comprehensive framework for the phased rollout of its Central Bank Digital Currency (CBDC), known as the e-Rupee or Digital Rupee. The pilot program is being expanded to 15 additional cities across India.\n\nThe CBDC framework operates on two tiers:\n\u2022 Wholesale CBDC (e\u20b9-W): For interbank settlements and large-value transactions between financial institutions. Already being piloted with 9 banks.\n\u2022 Retail CBDC (e\u20b9-R): For general public use, enabling person-to-person and person-to-merchant transactions.\n\nKey Features of the e-Rupee:\n- Offline transaction capability for areas with limited internet connectivity\n- Full interoperability with the Unified Payments Interface (UPI) ecosystem\n- Programmable money features enabling targeted government subsidies (e.g., fertilizer subsidy directly to farmers)\n- Privacy protection with limited anonymity for small transactions\n\nThe RBI has partnered with SBI, HDFC Bank, ICICI Bank, and other major banks to distribute the digital currency through existing banking infrastructure. The e-Rupee is designed to complement, not replace, physical currency.\n\nIMPORTANCE FOR UPSC:\nThe CBDC is important from the perspective of monetary policy, financial inclusion, and digital governance. It reduces the cost of currency management, promotes financial inclusion, and can enhance the efficiency of the payment system.","",b,A.a(["RBI designs CBDC framework","Wholesale pilot (e\u20b9-W) \u2014 9 banks","Retail pilot (e\u20b9-R) \u2014 public use","UPI integration for seamless payments","Offline capability for rural areas","Expansion to 15+ cities","Programmable subsidies enabled"],b8),"","a3","https://picsum.photos/seed/rbi_digital_rupee/800/400",!0,q,B.bW,"e-RUPEE: e=Electronic, R=RBI issued, U=UPI compatible, P=Programmable, E=Exchange offline, E=Existing banks distribute",a4,B.ag,c3,p,c1,"","The Reserve Bank of India expands the e-Rupee (CBDC) pilot to 15 more cities, outlining a two-tier wholesale and retail framework with UPI interoperability.","","RBI Introduces e-Rupee: India's Central Bank Digital Currency",a1)
