n=A.iZ("Expected in Mains GS-II (Governance) and GS-III (IT). Compare DPDP with GDPR, understand consent manager concept, and implications for Aadhaar and surveillance.","",m,"","The Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act, 2023, received Presidential assent and represents India's first comprehensive legislation on data privacy and protection. The Act establishes a framework for the processing of digital personal data.\n\nKey Definitions:\n\u2022 Data Fiduciary: Entity that determines the purpose and means of processing personal data\n\u2022 Data Principal: The individual whose data is being processed\n\u2022 Data Processor: Entity that processes data on behalf of the data fiduciary\n\u2022 Consent Manager: Registered entity that manages consent on behalf of data principals\n\nCore Provisions:\n1. Consent-Based Processing: Personal data can only be processed for lawful purposes with the individual's free, informed, and specific consent\n2. Rights of Data Principals: Right to access, correction, erasure, and grievance redressal\n3. Obligations of Data Fiduciaries: Reasonable security safeguards, data breach notification, data retention limits\n4. Significant Data Fiduciaries: Additional obligations including data protection impact assessment, independent data auditor, and Data Protection Officer\n5. Cross-Border Data Transfer: Allowed to all countries except those restricted by government notification\n6. Data Protection Board of India: Adjudicatory body to handle complaints and impose penalties\n\nPenalties:\n- Up to Rs 250 crore for failure to take security safeguards leading to a data breach\n- Up to Rs 200 crore for non-compliance with obligations regarding children's data\n- Up to Rs 150 crore for failure to notify the Board of a data breach","",b,A.a(["Data fiduciary collects personal data","Consent obtained from data principal","Data processed for lawful purpose only","Breach occurs \u2192 Board notified","DPB investigates complaint","Penalty imposed if non-compliant","Data principal can request erasure"],b8),"","a9","https://picsum.photos/seed/data_privacy_india/800/400",!1,k,B.bW,"DPDP: D=Data fiduciary, P=Principal rights, D=DPB adjudicates, P=Penalties Rs 250cr max","Livemint",B.ag,l,j,n,"","India enacts its first comprehensive data protection law establishing a Data Protection Board, consent-based processing, and significant penalties for violations.","","Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023: A New Data Privacy Framework",a3)
