k=A.iZ("Key for GS-III (Economy/Science). Understand why India needs domestic semiconductor manufacturing, global supply chain vulnerabilities (COVID chip shortage), and strategic significance for defense.","",j,"","The India Semiconductor Mission (ISM), announced under the Ministry of Electronics and IT, is a Rs 76,000 crore initiative to establish a comprehensive semiconductor manufacturing ecosystem in India.\n\nApproved Projects:\n1. Tata Electronics: Semiconductor fab in Dholera, Gujarat \u2014 India's first commercial semiconductor fab\n2. CG Power (in partnership with Renesas and Stars Microelectronics): OSAT (Outsourced Semiconductor Assembly and Test) facility in Sanand, Gujarat\n3. Tata Electronics: OSAT facility in Morigaon, Assam\n\nWhy Semiconductors Matter:\nSemiconductors are the backbone of modern technology \u2014 used in smartphones, computers, automobiles, defense systems, medical devices, and telecom infrastructure. The global semiconductor market is valued at over $600 billion.\n\nIndia's Current Position:\n- India imports nearly 100% of its semiconductor requirements\n- The global chip shortage (2020-22) highlighted supply chain vulnerabilities\n- India has a strong semiconductor design talent pool \u2014 20% of global chip designers are Indian\n\nStrategic Significance:\n- Reduces dependence on Taiwan, South Korea, and China for chip supply\n- Builds supply chain resilience for critical technology\n- Complements Make in India and Atmanirbhar Bharat initiatives\n- Creates over 1 lakh direct and indirect jobs\n- Key to India's digital economy and defense modernization goals","",b,A.a(["Global chip shortage exposes vulnerability","ISM announced with Rs 76,000 crore","Tata Electronics chip fab (Dholera, Gujarat)","OSAT facilities (Sanand + Morigaon)","Design talent leveraged (20% global share)","Reduces import dependency","Ecosystem: Design \u2192 Fabrication \u2192 Assembly \u2192 Testing"],b8),"","a12","https://picsum.photos/seed/semiconductor_india/800/400",!1,h,B.bW,"ISM: I=India's first fab (Dholera), S=Seventy-six thousand crore, M=Manufacturing ecosystem; TAT=Tata leads",a4,B.ag,i,g,k,"","India Semiconductor Mission approves Rs 76,000 crore for chip fab units, with Tata and CG Power partnerships to establish semiconductor manufacturing in Gujarat and Assam.","","India's Semiconductor Mission: Building a Chip Manufacturing Ecosystem",a1)
